2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
¾ cup Basmati Rice
56 g Green Peas
1 unit(s) Carrot
113 g Mushrooms
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
¼ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 tbsp Beef Stock Powder
1 tbsp Cream Sauce Spice Blend
2 tbsp Garlic Spread
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Once water is boiling, add rice and green peas, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, quarter mushrooms.
Peel, then halve carrot lengthwise. Cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then carrots and 3 tbsp (6 tbsp) water. Cook, stirring often, until carrots are tender-crisp and water evaporates, 5-7 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Transfer veggies to a plate, then cover to keep warm.

Reheat the same pan (from step 2) over medium.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then Beyond Meat® patties. (NOTE: Don't overcrowd the pan; cook patties in 2 batches if needed, using 1/2 tbsp oil per batch.) Pan-fry until golden-brown and cooked through, 4-5 min per side.**
Remove from heat.
Transfer Beyond Meat® patties to another plate, then cover to keep warm.
Carefully wipe the pan clean with paper towels.

Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, then swirl the pan to melt. Add mushrooms and onions. Cook until softened, 5-6 min.
Sprinkle Cream Sauce Spice Blend and remaining stock powder over top. Cook, stirring often, until coated, 30 sec.
Gradually whisk in 3/4 cup (1 1/4 cups) water. Cook, stirring often, until sauce comes to a simmer.
Once simmering, whisk often, until sauce thickens slightly, 1-2 min.

Fluff rice with a fork.
Divide rice, Beyond Meat® patties and veggies between bowls.
Spoon mushroom gravy over patties.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, skip the instructions to form the patties.

Cook Beyond Meat® the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the beef and pork mix.

Cuire le Beyond Meat® de la même façon que la recette vous indique de cuire le mélange